text.tspan: User Personas
Rebecca Warren
• Follows social media trends
• Last minute shopper
• Constantly looking for inspiration for styling clothes
• Style is more important the price or quality
Trend Chaser
• Doesn’t have the money to pay for designer clothing
• Never plans ahead when in need of new clothing for events.
• Finds themselves on less that trusted websites in order to find what she needs.
• Has trouble returning items to websites due to lack of customer service
Frustrations
• Offer on unique options with better quality at competetive prices to fast fashion websites.
• Offer option to opt in to newsletter of new styles and collections available.
• Ensure trust with customers by offering creating a profile as well as sending confirmation emails with
personalized language.
Solutions
“I tend to lean more towards fast
fashion because they are
within my budget but the clothing
never lasts more than a few
months”
• Searches for interesting and unique peices
• Invests in good quality fabric.
• Constantly looking for inspiration for styling clothes
• Quality is more important that style or price.
Fashion Forward
Frustrations
• Offer links to social media sites featuring unique fashions.
• Offer quality clothing at competitive prices to fast fashion websites.
• Offer styling inspiration for unique peices offered on website.
• Offer information of fabric and matierals used on each clothing.
Solutions
“I don’t mind spending money on
a peice if that item will
last me through the years.”
Adeline Stanley
• Too many fast fashion websites permiate social media and search engines.
• Isn’t able to update wardrobe very often due to dislike for cheap fabric and quality
fabrics being too expensive
• Hates wearing what everyone else is wearing.
Practical Shopper
Frustrations
• Curate a collection based on basics and offer inspiration photos to inspire users to purchase.
• Offer clothing at compettive prices to fast fashion websites but ensure qualty material by listing off
material of products.
• Inspire users to try different peices one wouldn’t normally purchase by offering inspiration photos or
blogs featuring certain collections.
Solutions
“I basically need new t-shirts and
jeans, but I wouldn’t mind
buying something fancy every
now and again.”
John Fields
• Looks for practical clothing
• Doesn’t really care for trends or unique clothing peices.
• Looks for deals on pracitcal everyday peices.
• Price is more important that quality or style.
• No one ever advertises for quality practical clothing, making it hard to create a
wardrobe one feels comfotable in.
• When he does come across a quality website, they sell overpriced quality clothing.
• Eventually wants to have a stylish wardrobe, but fast fashion websites clothing are
intimidating do to loud trend styles.
